{
  "stem": "2118.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Of course, nobody could stop you from praying at home, but you had to hide, you know, not stay in the window and pray.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And so they dissolved the-- the Jewish committee, or the Kehillah, and on the 11th of November, which was Polish Independence Day, we woke up in the morning, and everybody was all excited.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They-- they torched the two last synagogues in the city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "First, there was an explosion.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They-- on the-- on the main square was a statue of Tadeusz Kosciuszko.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He was a revolutionary.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He got up against the revolution in-- I don't remember what year it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he was a very famous hero in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So they blew up his statue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And in the same day, the same night, they burned the-- the orthodox synagogue and they burned the reformed synagogue.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, here it wouldn't be-- here it would be conservative.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Over there, it was reform.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We called it the German synagogue, because we used to-- I don't know why we called it the German, but I-- I imagine because the Germans were so far more reformed than we were.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And this was a very, very big tragedy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Of course, we didn't know what tragedies there is to follow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So on the next day, I went down to the-- to Independence Square to see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I was a boy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They told me not to go, but I was a boy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Who's going to bother a boy, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So I went down, and they laid him out on the ground, and they put up a barrier-- not a barrier, but like a-- like a-- a string strung out around him.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And you could go around in a circle and see him, you know, how he was laid down there.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
